		},
		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "Recent work has shown success \r",
			"relation": "bg-compare"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "in using neural network language models ( NNLMs ) as features in MT systems . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "Here , we present a novel formulation for a neural network joint model ( NNJM ) , \r",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "which augments the NNLM with a source context window . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "Our model is purely lexicalized \r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "and can be integrated into any MT decoder . <S>\r",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "We also present several variations of the NNJM \r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "which provide significant additive improvements . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "Although the model is quite simple , \r",
			"relation": "contrast"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "it yields strong empirical results . <S>\r",
			"relation": "evaluation"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "On the NIST OpenMT12 Arabic-English condition , the NNJM features produce a gain of +3.0 BLEU on top of a powerful , feature-rich baseline \r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "which already includes a target-only NNLM . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "The NNJM features also produce a gain of +6.3 BLEU on top of a simpler baseline equivalent to Chiang's (2007) original Hiero implementation . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "Additionally , we describe two novel techniques \r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "for overcoming the historically high cost of using NNLM-style models in MT decoding . <S>\r",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "These techniques speed up NNJM computation by a factor of 10,000x , \r",
			"relation": "evaluation"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 16,
			"text": "making the model as fast as a standard back-off LM . <S>\r",
			"relation": "comparison"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "This work was supported by DARPA/I2O Contract HR0011-12-C-0014 under the BOLT program \r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
